Why do we tell actors to "break a leg"? Because every play needs a cast! 

One day, while trying to make coffee, I realized the machine was like me before coffee: not quite awake. Then I saw the note: "Out of order. Even coffee machines need a coffee to function right!"

One joined, stating, "Some days I feel like that coffee machine too—brewed out and needing a recharge."

"Ah, well," said Two, "at least we can all agree that life's better with a good cup of coffee!"

Why did the coffee file a police report? It got mugged! 

When it tried to call 911, it spilled the beans!

And then it wanted to espresso its feelings, but the line was too frothy!

At least the donut was there to give it some crumby advice.

Now they brew up a plan to catch the perp every morning!

Who's watching their back? The cream of the crop detective.

That detective surely has a latte on his plate!

But they know they'll grind through it, one cup at a time.
